🎲 Simple Dice Roller

This is a simple Python program that simulates rolling a dice. It generates a random number between 1 and 6 each time you run it.

🚀 How It Works

The program uses Python’s random module.

Each roll generates a random number between 1 and 6.

You can choose to roll again or exit.

🖥️ How to Run

Make sure you have Python 3 installed.

Save the code as main.py.

Run the file in your terminal:

python main.py